comment.narrative:
Voters Education and Publicity Improved
1.Design, Development & Dissemination of Strategic Communication for Voter’s Education and Publicity (VEP) through radio and television (In close coordination with Inter-Agency Committee on Civic Education) and Election Observation .
2. Support to INEC to organize capacity building on gender-responsive electoral management and sensitization of INEC Staff;
3.Support to development of gender sensitive voter outreach materials both for voters and women candidates;
4.Capacity building on gender mainstreaming for CSOs and other existing national and community-based monitoring mechanisms to facilitate VAWE monitoring and prevention strategies;
5.	Capacity building and advocacy with political parties on gender equality and violence-free political processes. 
6.  Increased Community and Civic Understanding of gender equality and women’s rights to political participation through advocacy and social mobilization

Support to Strategic and Operational Planning by INEC 
Key Activities
1.	Support to post-election assessments;
2.	Finalization of the INEC Report;
3.	Validation of INEC Final Report. 
4..	Implementation of national-level training and capacity building targeting women aspirants and nominated candidates;
5.	Roll-out of election journey guide countrywide to support women candidates and aspirants;
6.	Convene two meetings in the run-up to the 2019 elections with women in business and professional groups;
7.	Provide induction training through workshops, for newly elected women leaders.
